<TEXT>
a swarm of bees attacked a group of 
young campers on a nature hike stinging several of them up to a 
dozen times and sending 12 children to hospitals authorities said 
all we could do was run and swat said stephen hill 10 who 
was stung in the back neck and arms 
twelve of the 30 children suffering stings were hospitalized 
briefly and released in good condition said spokesmen for 
university community hospital in tampa and east pasco medical 
center in zephyrhills 
you could literally almost pull the insects off of them 
said shari brown head counselor for tampas palnez summer day camp 
a group of 42 children ages 6 to 11 and counselors were 
exploring the rapids trail in hillsborough river state park when 
they were suddenly attacked by the swarm 
during the onslaught youngsters scattered screaming through the 
woods trying to get off the trail ms brown said two of the four 
counselors were stung several times as they attempted to round up 
the hysterical children 
a few of the children who had run ahead of the group may have 
disturbed the bees which could have been feeding or defending a 
nearby hive park manager perry smith said adding that he didnt 
know what kind of bees they were 
park personnel who later walked the trail could find no sign of 
the bees or a hive 
</TEXT>
