crude and heating oil prices rose but gasoline 
prices declined in light preweekend trading that brokers 
attributed largely to internal market influences 
on the new york mercantile exchange the augustdelivery price 
for west texas intermediate advanced 10 cents a barrel on friday to 
1486 
among refined products traded on the exchange wholesale no 2 
heating oil rose 021 cent a gallon to 4112 cents and unleaded 
gasoline fell 081 cent a gallon to 4973 cents 
brokers said crude and heating oil prices rose partly from 
shortcovering the purchase of contracts by speculators to replace 
borrowed contracts they had sold earlier shortcovering can cause 
shortterm price rises 
others attributed the advances partly to a tendency by many 
traders to reduce risky positions heading into a weekend weve 
got a lot of people squaring up their books said peter beutel 
assistant director at elders futures inc a new york 
energyfutures trading concern 
traders said the decline in gasoline came from preweekend 
profit taking contrary to recent declines in oil prices gasoline 
has been rising sharply because of unprecedented demand and tight 
supplies in the united states 
